Any student requesting credit recovery for Spring 2020 please meet at JHS at 9am Monday, June 22.

You will be required to work 1 hour at JHS per week and the rest you can do remotely.

Laptops are also available if needed.

JHS will use the Acellus format for this one-time situation.

Credit Recovery through Acellus will be Pass/Fail only. No grades will be awarded

shared_text:
Dawn Pierce added 481 new photos to the album: JHS Graduating Class of 2020.
June 1 at 5:55 PM ¬∑

On March 16th...our first school day away from the school thanks to Covid-19, it was looking like we were not going to get a Graduation Ceremony. I can imagine what was going through these seniors heads when they got wind of that....12 years worth of blood, sweat and tears and no celebration? Our amazing administration and Senior Class Advisors said, "hold my coffee", and pulled of an absolutely AMAZING celebration of our seniors and their families! I am soo proud to be part of this amazing JHS family, they always put the students and their families first (with safety in mind)!! I hope you enjoy the photos, there are a ton of them!

Cassidy Parsons is feeling proud at Jefferson High School.
May 28 at 11:27 AM ¬∑ Boulder, MT ¬∑

Once again I am so proud of Josh, Hayden, and Jamie!! They were selected as Finalists in the AdCap Challenge!

They answered and developed a plan for the challenge question ‚ÄúHow would you re-think the space, the experience or meals served in your cafeteria to increase efficiency, decrease food waste, and encourage consumption of nutritious foods?‚Äù

As finalists they get $1000 to implement their idea and several other neat prizes! They also have a chance to double their prize money and be chosen as a grand prize winner. They will find that out on June 11th!

Scholarship Name: PNACAC Student Scholarship
Deadline: March 1st
Award: $500 - $1,000
Eligibility Locations: AK, ID, MT, OR, and WA
Scholarship is open to students currently enrolled in their senior year of high school and plans to attend a regionally accredited college or university in Fall 2020 OR currently enrolled students who attend a two-year college and plans to attend a regionally accredited college or university in Fall 2020. Applicant must submit a video on what they plan on doing in 10 years OR or how their college/career counselor has helped them in finding the right college fit. To learn more or to apply, please visit https://buff.ly/3853mJm

post_text: Our first Panther of the Week is a person who is very helpful to both staff and classmates- in the classroom, and especially in shop class. He has a good sense of humor and supports classmates and friends. In the words of his nominators- he does not have a mean bone in his body, and always looks on the bright side of things, even when he may has had reasons not to. Caleb Allen is our first Panther of the Week for 2020! Congratulations Caleb!

Quoting Mrs.Joliff
"We had a great time, but definitely missed having Talon with us!
The girls did great -
Kennedy Williams placed 3rd with her Original Oratory Speech
Quinne Shultz and Katie Conroy placed 3rd with their Public Forum Debate case.
If you see them, be sure to congratulate them! We were against 18 schools.
This week, we head to Lewistown."

post_text: This week our Panther of the Week is Ethan Smartnick. On Nov 22, Ethan was driving to Helena and a car had rolled and ejected its passengers. Ethan was able to help the passengers as he remained calm, kept the victims warm, and helped the paramedics, once they arrived, onto the spine boards for transport to Helena. Congratulations Ethan for helping someone in need and jumping right in, and doing what needed to be done and in the process possibly saving a life.
